article.headline: Pennsylvania 89, Siena 62
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Mark Zoller scored 18 points and Eric Osmundson added 17 to lift Penn to a 89-62 victory over Siena on Saturday. The Quakers (5-7) shot 58 percent from the floor and outrebounded the Saints 42-32. Osmundson started Penn off on a 9-2 run, scoring seven of his 17 points to open the game. With 12:30 remaining in the first half, the Quakers held a 20-point lead. Siena (3-12) closed to within 48-34 on an Al Fisher jump shot, but Penn blew the game wide open less than two minutes into the second half by going on a 12-3 run to take a 60-37 lead. Tim Begley added 11 points for Penn. Tay Fisher led Siena with 13 points and Michael Haddix added 12. It was the worst home loss for Siena since falling to Iona 91-58 in 1997.
